layout.p:
Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 20;
                                                  written lines: 20; Uniform layout. Four blank lines between the books of the Pentateuch and also between the Five Scrolls. Masorah magna on the Pentateuch and the Scrolls generally in two lines of the upper and three lines of the lower margin.The weekly sections marked with פרש' in the margin, a continuous enumeration of 54 sections being added in Hebrew letters.The commandments written in the margin or between the column where they respectively appear.No pricking currently visible. Ruling with hard point on the hair-side of folios.
